KPA Anniversary Marked Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- Lectures were given and film shows were held by the Ethiopian Youth Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association, the Palestinian Popular Struggle Front and the Secretariat of the Pan-African Movement from April 22 to 28 on the occasion of the 74th anniversary of the foundation of the Korean People's Army.
 "The Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks" and other Korean films were screened at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Ethiopian Youth Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea in a lecture said that the 70-odd-year history of the KPA is a proud history in which it has demonstrated the might of a strong army, holding the outstanding brilliant commanders in esteem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association, after appreciating the film, said that they were encouraged to see the invincible might of the KPA and they have come to know well the reason why the DPRK is confidently advancing along the road of socialism, not affected by the U.S. imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle it.
 The chief for External Relations of the Palestinian Popular Struggle Front who is also member of its Political Bureau noted that the film convinced him that nobody can match the might of the heroic KPA led by the iron-willed brilliant commander and the final victory is in store for the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the Financial Department of the Secretariat of the Pan-African Movement said that through the film he saw the disciplined and united army and people of the DPRK. No one will dare provoke the DPRK who has the army equipped with modern offensive and defensive means and strong people, the director added.

RS Calls for Training Many Competent Talents 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- Training many competent talents through vigorous revolution in education is an important work for the future of the country and the nation and a firm guarantee for building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation on the basis of modern science and technology as early as possible.
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important in training competent talents is to set a proper goal of training them to meet the requirements of the new century and improve the content and methods of education so as to attain it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To achieve the goal of education the content and methods of education should be improved to suit it. The improvement of the content of education requires to strictly select the basic and fundamental conception and give lessons on what is kernel while teaching methodology free from the outdated viewpoint of giving knowledge much in quantity. And it is very important to apply the heuristic method of teaching to education so as to make the students learn about knowledge by themselves.
 And what is important in bringing up talents is to intensify education in basic science and education of gifted children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il set forth the wise policy of intensifying education in the basic science of nature such as mathematics, physics, chemistry and biology as well as computer-aided education, instructing that education in basic science should be intensified in the field of education in order to develop sciences and technology and put IT and computerization of the national economy on a higher level.
 Education of gifted children is fundamental in training talents. It is important to select well gifted children and conduct education in a scientific way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To train many talents is very important and responsible work for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and the future of the country.

National Festival of Science and Technology Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The 21st National Festival of Science and Technology was held in Pyongyang from May 2 to 5.
 It involved a seminar on latest scientific and technological achievements, a public presentation of achievements in scientific researches and technological innovation and an exhibition of diagrams. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The national festival was preceded by the provincial, city and county festivals of science and technology to which tens of thousands of scientific and technological achievements were presented by officials, scientists, technicians and working people from different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 500 scientific and technological achievements which had been highly estimated at the provincial, city and county festivals were presented at 19 panel discussions including agricultural, power and metal industrial sectors and railway transport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the festival introduced scientific and technological achievements in various domains helpful to putting the ultra-modern technology and basic scientific and technological sectors and the technological engineering in major domains onto a higher level of development and accelerating the reconstruction and modernization of the national economy and exchanged their experience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the festival special prize went to the paper on the technology of cultivating a new variety of high-yielding paddy rice, the paper on a new type horizontal jib tower crane and three other papers while first place went to the paper on a technological measure for ensuring the highest efficiency and normal operation of wind-driven generator and 51 other papers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony of the national festival took place at Kim Chaek University of Technology on May 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Kim Yong Jin, minister of  Education, Pyon Yong Rip, president of the State Academy of Sciences, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the results of the national festival were announced by the jury, festival cups, medals and certificates were awarded to the successful participants in the festival.

RS on Paektu Revolutionary Traditions
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today devotes its one whole page to a by-lined article titled "Paektu revolutionary traditions are an eternal lifeline of Songun Korea". The article is published on the occasion of the 80th anniversary of the Down-with-Imperialism Union formed by President Kim Il Sung and the 50th anniversary of the study tour of the revolutionary battle sites in the area of Mt. Paektu started by leader Kim Jong Il.
 The article notes that the army and the people of the DPRK have dynamically stepped up the general march for the Songun revolution, regarding the Paektu revolutionary traditions as an eternal lifeline for accomplishing the cause of Juche.
 In its first part the article stresses that the above-said traditions established by the President serve as an invincible banner of eternal vitality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traditions are eternal guidelines for the revolution as they embody the principle of the Songun revolution which calls for exploring the road of revolution and winning its victory with arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of attaching importance to arms served as the kernel and starting point of all the lines and policies, strategies and tactics in the protracted course of the Korean revolution. The principle of Songun helped work out fundamental guidelines for building the party, the army and the state, lay down a strategy of giving importance to the ideology and achieving unity and  indicate the shortest cut to the social transformation, human remoulding and nature-remaking. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Paektu revolutionary traditions also mean the tradition of revolutionary comradeship and single-minded unity, and they serve as an ever-lasting weapon for successfully accomplishing the socialist cause in the present times as they contain rich experience gained in the Songun revolution and exploits performed in its course.
 The Korean revolution is a glorious revolution as it achieved the steel-like unity of the whole party and society deeply rooted in the Paektu traditions of single-minded unity and has always emerged victorious with its might. In this proud course, the traditions of the Korean revolution have been given steady continuity and our country has demonstrated its might as a powerful state that boasts the single-minded unity.
 In the second part, the article notes that the Korean revolution is sure to triumph as it has a great history and traditions and they have been steadfastly carried forward. 
 Kim Jong Il is the great protector and successor to the Paektu revolutionary traditions because he has directed utmost efforts to inheriting the revolutionary traditions, regarding this matter as essential for the victorious advance and accomplishment of the revolutionary cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 50 years ago, he started the study tour of revolutionary battle sites in the area of Mt. Paektu. And on Ryongnam Hill he made a historic pledge to creditably succeed to the revolutionary cause of Kim Il Sung. He thus made a new glorious history of inheriting the revolutionary traditions in the country, cherishing the unshakable faith in the Paektu revolutionary traditions established by the President.
 He is an iron-willed commander who has trained the People's Army to be the best protectors of the Paektu revolutionary traditions and invincible revolutionary armed forces of Mt. Paektu. He is, at the same time, a prominent and veteran leader who has prepared the 3rd and 4th generations of the Korean revolution as genuine heirs to the Paektu revolutionary traditions to give a steady continuity to the Songun revolution and created a heroic epic of the Songun era with the Paektu revolutionary spirit and fighting stamina. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the third part the article describes the ongoing general march for the Songun revolution as a heroic all-people march in the present times to win a final victory of the Songun cause by following up the march to Mt. Paektu started by the President.
 To fully display the vitality of the Paektu revolutionary traditions is a very important work for glorifying the history of the Korean revolution as a history of devotedly defending the leader forever, and a sacred struggle to give steady continuity to the history of the victorious Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also a worthwhile struggle to ensure the fresh and great progress of Korean-style socialism with conviction of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 21st century in which we advance under the guidance of Kim Jong Il will shine as a glorious century because the Songun cause of Juche will emerge victorious with the might of the Paektu revolutionary traditions and the country will achieve the greatest prosperity, the article concludes.

8th Pyongyang Medical Scientific Symposium Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The 8th Pyongyang medical scientific symposium of Koreans at home and abroad took place at the People's Palace of Culture from May 3 through 5.
 The symposium was attended by Choe Chang Sik, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Medical Association, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was also attended by a delegation of Korean medical scientists in Japan led by Ri Tae Guk, chairman of the Korean Medical Association in Japan, a delegation of Korean medical scientists in the U.S. led by Jo Jun Yong, associate professor of Balyor College of Dentistry, U.S., and a delegation of medical scientists of the south side led by Kim Se Gon, permanent vice-chairman of the south Korean Association of Doctors.
 Choe Chang Sik made an opening address which was followed by congratulatory speeches by heads of the delegations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symposium heard lectures given under the titles "On 'Ouichwalyobang', medical heritage dating back to the period of Koryo and its recovery", "Historical inquiry into minamata disease", "On revitalization medical science" and others.
 Then more than 70 valuable papers were presented at panel discussions involving basic science and oncology, surgical and dental diseases, internal and pediatric diseases and obstetrics and gynecology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The papers dealt with achievements and experience gained in solving scientific and technical problems pending urgent solutions in the medical treatment suited to the constitutional features of Koreans and the practical health care and in introducing state-of-the-art science and technology to preventing and treating diseases in keeping with the global trend of the rapidly developing medical science and technology.
 The symposium also discussed the issue of how the Korean medical scientists in the north and the south and abroad should conduct exchange and cooperation in the field of medical science as required by the June 15 era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Souvenirs and certificates were awarded to the heads of the delegations and those who presented excellent papers.
